{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"161782fd-7b1c-41f2-8bde-8a2acd8f2227","content":"Yes, both are known MSTest v4 breaking changes. Here's what's happening:\n\n---\n\n### 1. Lost test history in Azure DevOps\n\nMSTest v4 changed the default **TestIdGenerationStrategy** from `DisplayName` to `FullyQualified`. Azure DevOps tracks history by test ID, so every test looks new. To restore history, add to your `.runsettings`:\n\n```xml\n<RunSettings>\n  <MSTest>\n    <TestIdGenerationStrategy>DisplayName</TestIdGenerationStrategy>\n  </MSTest>\n</RunSettings>\n```\n\n---\n\n### 2. `TestContext.TestName` in `[ClassInitialize]`\n\nIn v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` is now a **class-level context** — it isn't associated with any specific test. Accessing `TestName` (line 13 in your code) throws because no test is running yet.\n\n**Fix:** Remove the `TestName` usage from `ClassInit`. If you need per-test setup, move that logic to `[TestInitialize]`:\n\n```csharp\n[TestInitialize]\npublic void TestInit()\n{\n    var testName = TestContext.TestName; // works here\n    // per-test setup\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. Other v4 things to watch for\n\n| Area | Change |\n|---|---|\n| **`[ClassCleanup]` timing** | Now defaults to `EndOfClass` (was `EndOfAssembly` in v3). Cleanup runs earlier. |\n| **Removed APIs** | Several long-deprecated `TestContext` members (like `DataRow`, `DataConnection`) were removed. |\n| **Parallel execution** | v4 enables method-level parallelism by default. Tests that relied on serial execution may now race. Control with `[assembly: Parallelize(Scope = ExecutionScope.ClassLevel)]` or disable entirely. |\n| **Assert behavioral changes** | `Assert.AreEqual` for floating-point comparisons and `Assert.ThrowsException` matching are stricter. |\n| **Source generators** | v4 uses source generators instead of reflection for test discovery. Non-public test classes/methods that worked before may now be silently skipped. |","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"5b2c90f8-f9f2-4ff6-b1b5-10518065d065","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"Now I can see the user's code and understand both issues. Let me provide a comprehensive answer about MSTest v4 breaking changes.\n\n1. **Test history lost in Azure DevOps**: In MSTest v4, the default fully qualified test ID format changed. Previously test IDs were based on the simple method name; now they use a fully qualified name. Azure DevOps matches test history by test ID, so when the IDs change, all tests appear as \"new.\" The fix is to set `<TestIdGenerationStrategy>` to `DisplayName` or the legacy value.\n\nActually, let me be more precise. In MSTest v3, the default `TestIdGenerationStrategy` was `DisplayName`. In MSTest v4, the default changed to `FullyQualified`. \n\nTo restore the old behavior and preserve test history, I need to add a configuration setting that reverts the test ID generation strategy back to using display names. This can be done either through a `.runsettings` file or directly in the project settings.\n\n2. **TestContext.TestName in [ClassInitialize]**: In MSTest v4, the `TestContext` passed to `[ClassInitialize]` operates at the class level rather than being tied to a specific test method. Since no individual test is running during class initialization, accessing `TestName` throws an exception because there's no test context to reference. In v3, this might have returned a value or handled it differently.\n\nThe solution is to avoid using `TestContext.TestName` within `[ClassInitialize]` methods.\n\nI should also cover some other significant breaking changes in v4 that users might encounter: the `TestContext` behavior shift, lifecycle changes for assembly and class initialization/cleanup, potential differences in parallel execution defaults, behavioral updates to `Assert.ThrowsException`, removal of deprecated APIs, and the shift in `TestIdGenerationStrategy` defaulting to `FullyQualified` instead of `DisplayName`.","outputTokens":1035,"requestId":"6802:2D5697:1C26DD6:1FCDDC1:69FD54BF"},"id":"c52673db-7df0-4d6d-811c-fcb921003076","timestamp":"2026-05-08T03:13:26.912Z","parentId":"0d614f84-2121-40f1-92e7-18af6b87b8ba"}
